 bias toward mercy—all delivered in crisp and lively new translations, and with the original Latin on facing pages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFairness. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aActivism.  aAnecdote.  aAwareness.  aAyn Rand.  aCapitalism.  aCicero.  aConsequentialism.  aConservatism.  aCruelty.  aDistributive justice.  aEpistle.  aEssay.  aFoolishness.  aFor a New Liberty.  aForbearance.  aForgiveness.  aGenerosity.  aGratitude.  aIntellectual.  aIntention.  aIntersectionality.  aLeft-libertarianism.  aLegitimacy (political).  aLibertarianism.  aMagnanimity.  aMeanness.  aMoral relativism.  aMorality.  aMurray Rothbard.  aNatural and legal rights.  aOrganization.  aOrganizing principle.  aOwnership.  aPaleolibertarianism.  aPardon.  aPerson.  aPhilosopher.  aPity.  aPolitical alliance.  aPractical Ethics.  aPremise.  aPrerogative.  aPrinciple.  aPunishment.  aReactionary.  aReality.  aReason.  aResult.  aReverence (emotion).  aRight to property.  aRobert Nozick.  aSchool of thought.  aSelf-awareness.  aSelf-ownership.  aSensibility.  aSocial justice.  aSocialism.  aSpontaneous order.  aState socialism.  aStoicism.  aThe Ethics of Liberty.  aThe Other Hand.  aThe Road to Serfdom.  aThought.  aTrait theory.  aTreatise.  aValue (ethics).  aWell-being.  aWound.  aWriting.1 aKaster, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2023